# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# .dockerignore — Exclude files from the Docker build context
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# When you run 'docker build', Docker sends all files in the build context
# to the Docker daemon. Large contexts = slow builds.
# .dockerignore works like .gitignore — excluded files are NOT sent.
#
# WHAT TO EXCLUDE:
#   node_modules/ — large (~500MB), rebuilt inside the container anyway
#   dist/         — compiled output, rebuilt inside the container
#   .env          — NEVER include secrets in a Docker image
#   .git/         — git history, useless inside the image
#   coverage/     — test coverage reports, not needed at runtime
#   *.md          — documentation, not needed at runtime

node_modules/
dist/
.env
*.md
.git/
coverage/
.DS_Store
*.log
npm-debug.log*
